rComments: Fantastic prof. Truly cares about her students, very approachable and helpful. Knows material very, very well. Always prepared for class and her powerpoint slides are so pretty (just like her.) Would highly recommend this class and prof to anyone. UofT is super lucky to have her.

This was one of my favorite classes by far in all 4 years at U of T. I took this course w. no interest in immigration but Professor Tran changed all that. She is A GODDESS on this otherwise abysmal campus. Knew all the students by name and her lectures were inspiring and fascinating. Take her class you won't regret it

I have never been so challenged in a class but also learned so much. I didn't know much about immigration before taking this class but the topics she teaches and the way she teaches them always keep the class focused. She's organized, inspirational and caring. The readings are actually pretty interesting too. Hope she teaches again!

My friend is in this class with me and we both wish every class could be like hers. It isn't about memorizing or taking exams but actually understanding the material and applying to real-life issues. Her assignments make you to think about the class lectures in a way that you haven't before. Prof. Tran is amazing and so smart but also so humble!

There are zero exams for this course. Expectations from Grace is ambiguous and the assignments are rather a nuisance than beneficial which will hurt your grade. 'Blog posts' and creating a syllabus as assignments are prime examples of the inexperience she has. Material is common sense issues on migration, citizenship, and belonging. Avoid TA/Prof
